Entry.JapaneseText: <Mao>……まだ昔の事は 思い出せそうにないか？
Entry.EnglishText: <Mao>... Do you still remember nothing of your past?

Entry.JapaneseText: ……うん……全然…… 思い出さなきゃダメなのかな？
Entry.EnglishText: ...Nope, not one thing... Maybe I just... can't remember?

Entry.JapaneseText: 無理をする必要はないが、 記憶が戻るに越した事はない。
Entry.EnglishText: You don't need to push yourself, but it would be nice for you to get your memories back.

Entry.JapaneseText: ボク的には思い出さなくても平気なんだけどな。 <Eugene>といる今が楽しいし。
Entry.EnglishText: Well, I'm okay with not remembering. I'm having fun being with you, <Eugene>.

Entry.JapaneseText: だが、おまえの家族や知り合いは 心配しているかもしれん。
Entry.EnglishText: But you might have friends and family that are worried about you.

Entry.JapaneseText: そっか……まあ、きっとなるようになるヨ！
Entry.EnglishText: I guess... Oh well, whatever will be, will be!

Entry.JapaneseText: 旅をしてれば、ボクの家族とも 会えるかもしれないし。
Entry.EnglishText: Who knows, maybe we'll run into my family on our travels.
